      <text xml:space="preserve" bytes="837">The '''sacramental index''' is a [[statistic]] sometimes used by [[Roman Catholic]] [[Bishop#Bishops in the Roman Catholic, Orthodox, and Anglican churches|bishops]] as a rough approximation of how active a [[parish]] is, based on the occurrence of [[sacrament]]s or [[rite of passage|rites of passage]].  The precise formula varies; in  the [[Archdiocese]] of [[Boston, Massachusetts|Boston]], the sacramental index for a parish is calculated by adding the total numbers of [[baptism]]s and [[funeral]]s, and twice the number of [[Christian view of marriage|weddings]].

The index is used to help determine the number of priests assigned to a parish.

==External links==
* [http://www.rcab.org/Parish_Reconfiguration/FAQ.html Archdiocese of Boston document including an index definition]

